    "plan_content": "Here's a summary of the plan:\n\n## Plan: Stepper Compound Component\n\n### What gets created (2 new files)\n1. **`apps/v4/registry/new-york-v4/ui/stepper.tsx`** — The full compound component\n2. **`apps/v4/registry/new-york-v4/examples/stepper-demo.tsx`** — A 3-step horizontal onboarding wizard demo\n\n### What gets modified (2 registry config files)\n3. **`ui/_registry.ts`** — Insert `stepper` entry between `spinner` and `switch` (after line 563)\n4. **`examples/_registry.ts`** — Insert `stepper-demo` entry between `spinner-item` and `switch-demo` (after line 2124)\n\n### Component Architecture\n- **7 sub-components**: `Stepper`, `StepperItem`, `StepperTrigger`, `StepperTitle`, `StepperDescription`, `StepperSeparator`, `StepperContent`\n- **No Radix UI dependency** — pure React context (mirrors `carousel.tsx` pattern)\n- **Dual context**: root `StepperContext` for orientation/active step + `StepperItemContext` per step for value/disabled/completed\n- **Controlled + uncontrolled** support via `value`/`defaultValue`/`onValueChange`\n- **Both orientations**: horizontal (`flex-row` items with growing `h-px` separator) and vertical (`flex-col` items with `w-px` vertical separator aligned to trigger center)\n- **`StepperContent`** works both nested inside `<StepperItem>` (reads item context) and standalone with its own `value` prop\n\n### Demo\nShows a 3-step \"Account → Profile → Review\" wizard with numbered circles (→ checkmarks on completion), `StepperSeparator` connectors, `StepperContent` panels per step, and Next/Back navigation buttons.",
